ueled a debate over gender and whether athletes withDifferences of Sexual Development(DSD) should compete in women's sport.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9998250978814253, \"rank\": 0.00017493271465553536, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 1481, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"score\": 0.9995328378205288, \"rank\": 0.00046738052205683785, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Direct_Stream_Digital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"British author J.K. Rowling, who has been outspoken on gender issues in the past, tweeted after the bout that the Paris Olympics had been \\\"forever tarnished by the brutal injustice done to Carini.\\\"\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1520, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9999999993910933, \"rank\": 5.599613339792545e-10, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 1535, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.256431030197729e-17, \"text\": \"J.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\"}, {\"begin\": 1709, \"end\": 1715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9998250978814253, \"rank\": 0.00017493271465553536, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC), said it wassaddened by the row, and that the pair were facing \\\"aggression\\\" because of an arbitrary decision.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1723, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It stressed all athletes competing in boxing met eligibility requirements, and that the IBA decision to disqualify the two boxers last year was a sudden and arbitrary decision, taken \\\"without any due process.\\\"\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9950460761548995, \"rank\": 0.004920050049378746, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin is a double world champion competing in her second Olympics, and will fight in the 57kg women's event against Uzbekistan's Sitora Turdibekova on Friday.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2197, \"end\": 2207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999413466883, \"rank\": 5.8404377447608906e-08, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin reportedly first started boxing after seeing her mother suffer domestic abuse.\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pan Men-an, the Secretary-General for Taiwan's Presidential office, said on Facebook he supported Lin and that it was wrong for her to be \\\"subjected to humiliation, insults and verbal bullying just because of your appearance and a controversial verdict in the past.\\\"\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2362, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9402895537988362, \"rank\": 0.06335493006203588, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tsai, the former president, also said on X that Lin was \\\"fearless in the face of challenges, whether they come from inside or outside the ring.\\\"\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2791, \"entities\": []}]}"